<div id="p549" class="blockpost rowodd">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#3&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=549#p549">Today 04:10:43</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=89612">George</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Member</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: Discussion of BEP 16: Superseeding</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>IMHO the current superseeding proposal is an ugly hack job, it's just abusing HAVE messages. <br /><br />Much better would be to have a separate message (ALLOWED_PIECE) to tell which piece a client is allowed to download, requests for other ones would be rejected. Clients who are not superseeders should send an ALLOWED_PIECE with 0xFFFFFFFF as value, to indicate all chunks are allowed. <br /><br />Support for this would be indicated by a bit in the handshake. Clients who do not support it, should be treated in the old way.<br /><br />You could use SUGGEST_PIECE for this, but a suggestion does not imply that the other pieces are of limits, while allowed does.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
			<div class="postfootleft"><p>Offline</p></div>
			<div class="postfootright"><div>&nbsp;</div></div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

